<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Lauren Lee</title>

  <style>
    :root {
      --cream: #f7f1e8;
      --yellow: #f2d85b;
      --orange: #ff5a2f;
      --charcoal: #25231f;
      --soft: #756c61;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      background: var(--cream);
      color: var(--charcoal);
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    main {
      max-width: 760px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 38px 22px 70px;
    }

    .hero {
      min-height: 86vh;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .tiny {
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: .18em;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: var(--soft);
      margin-bottom: 28px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      font-size: clamp(70px, 19vw, 138px);
      line-height: .82;
      letter-spacing: -0.08em;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .subtitle {
      margin-top: 28px;
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: clamp(30px, 8vw, 58px);
      line-height: .95;
      color: var(--yellow);
      max-width: 620px;
    }

    .intro {
      margin-top: 32px;
      font-size: 21px;
      line-height: 1.35;
      color: var(--soft);
      max-width: 560px;
    }

    .arrow {
      margin-top: 42px;
      font-size: 34px;
      color: var(--orange);
    }

    .section {
      padding: 52px 0;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(37, 35, 31, .18);
    }

    h2 {
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      font-size: clamp(42px, 10vw, 78px);
      line-height: .9;
      letter-spacing: -0.06em;
      margin: 0 0 18px;
    }

    p {
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.45;
      color: var(--soft);
      margin: 0 0 24px;
      max-width: 570px;
    }

    a.button {
      display: inline-block;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: var(--charcoal);
      border: 1px solid var(--charcoal);
      border-radius: 999px;
      padding: 13px 22px;
      font-size: 15px;
      transition: all .2s ease;
    }

    a.button:hover {
      background: var(--yellow);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }

    .note {
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--orange);
    }

    .closing {
      padding: 92px 0 34px;
    }

    .closing h2 {
      color: var(--orange);
    }

    footer {
      color: var(--soft);
      font-size: 13px;
      padding-top: 40px;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <main>

    <section class="hero">
      <div class="tiny">Building work I love</div>

      <h1>Lauren<br>Lee</h1>

      <div class="subtitle">
        Following the threads of building work I love.
      </div>

      <p class="intro">
        For the people who can no longer ignore the creative ideas that keep finding them.
      </p>

      <div class="arrow">↓</div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Continue</h2>
      <p>Conversations on intuition, creativity, and being human.</p>
      <a class="button" href="#" target="_blank">Listen in</a>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Intuitive Readings</h2>
      <p>
        Grounded one-on-one sessions. No predicting. No weird pressure.
        Just connection, conversation, and whatever unfolds.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="#" target="_blank">Book a session</a>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>The Art of Mindfulness for Creatives</h2>
      <p>
        A gentle course for people learning to trust themselves and build work they love.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="#" target="_blank">Join the waitlist</a>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Field Notes</h2>
      <p>
        Books. Ideas. Observations. The threads I can’t stop following lately.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="#" target="_blank">Read along</a>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Say hello</h2>
      <p>
        Podcast guests. Readings. Collaborations. Questions.
        Or just a little hello.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="mailto:leelaure@gmail.com">Email me</a>
    </section>

    <section class="closing">
      <h2>It’s your turn.</h2>
      <p class="note">To trust the thing that keeps finding you.</p>
    </section>

    <footer>
      © Lauren Lee
    </footer>

  </main>
</body>
</html>
